We use a LinkedList for the stack data structure, which has a constant time complexity for push and pop operations (O(1)). We also maintain a separate variable for the minimum element, which also has a constant time complexity (O(1)). The top() and getMin() methods simply return the values from the stack and minimum element variables respectively, which have a time complexity of O(1).

